ies&f=false|title=Encyclopedia of Television|editor=Horace Newcomb|publisher=[[Routledge]]|location=[[Abingdon-on-Thames]]|year=2004|edition=2nd|isbn=978-1579583941|page=60}}\n* {{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=U1Pe45NhU08C&pg=PA460&lpg=PA460&dq=3+Girls+3+1977+tv+series#v=twopage&q=3%20Girls%203%201977%20tv%20series&f=false|title=The A to Z of African-American Television (The A to Z Guide Series)|last=Fearn-Banks|first=Kathleen|publisher=[[Rowman & Littlefield#Imprints|Scarecrow Press]]|location=[[Lanham, Maryland]]|edition=49th|year=2009|isbn=978-0810868328|page=460}}\n* {{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wxa7BAAAQBAJ&pg=PA488&lpg=PA488&dq=3+Girls+3+1977+tv+series#v=twopage&q=3%20Girls%203%201977%20tv%20series&f=false|title=Historical Dictionary of African-American Television (Historical Dictionaries of Literature and the Arts)|last=Fearn-Banks|first=Kathleen|publisher=[[Rowman & Littlefield#Imprints|Scarecrow Press]]|location=[[Lanham, Maryland]]|year=2005|isbn=978-0810853355|page=488}}\n* {{cite journal|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LEAEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA3&lpg=PA3&dq=Here%27s+to+you,+Mrs.+Hamilton#v=twopage&q=Here's%20to%20you%2C%20Mrs.%20Hamilton&f=false|first=Joan|last=Downs|title=Here's to you, Mrs. Hamilton|journal=[[Life (magazine)|Life]]|publisher=[[Time Inc.]]|location=United States|volume=70|issue=18|date=May 14, 1971|accessdate=October 14, 2016|pages=93\u201397}}\n* {{cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/onemoretimememoiburn00burn/page/194|title=One More Time: A Memoir By Carol Burnett|last=Burnett|first=Carol|authorlink=Carol Burnett|year=1986|publisher=[[Random House]]|location=[[New York City]]|isbn=978-0394552545|edition=1st|pages=[https://archive.org/details/onemoretimememoiburn00burn/page/194 194\u2013195]}}\n* {{cite magazine|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ziMAAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA177&lpg=PA177&dq=1974+film+based+on+Ben+Hecht+and+Charles+MacArthur%27s+play+of+the+same+name#v=twopage&q=1974%20film%20based%20on%20Ben%20Hecht%20and%20Charles%20MacArthur's%20play%20of%20the%20same%20name&f=false|title=Television Highlights|magazine=[[New York (magazine)|New York]]|publisher=New York Media, LLC|location=[[New York City]]|date=August 30, 1993|page=177}}\n* {{cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/leonardmaltins2000leon/page/587|last=Maltin|first=Leonard|title=Leonard Maltin's Movie Guide 2008|chapter=Health|page=[https://archive.org/details/leonardmaltins2000leon/page/587 587]|isbn=978-0451221865|year=2007|publisher=[[New American Library|Signet Books]]|location=[[New York City]]}}\n* {{cite book|last=O'Brien|first=Daniel|url=https://www.amazon.com/Robert-Altman-Hollywood-Daniel-OBrien/dp/0826407919|title=Robert Altman: Hollywood Survivor|isbn=0-8264-0791-9|year=1995|location=New York|publisher=Continuum|page=135}}\n* {{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JUzIAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA365&lpg=PA365&dq=Sills+and+Burnett+at+the+Met+(TV+Movie)#v=twopage&q=Sills%20and%20Burnett%20at%20the%20Met%20(TV%20Movie)&f=false|title=Encyclopedia of Television|editor=Horace Newcomb|publisher=[[Routledge]]|location=[[Abingdon-on-Thames]]|year=2004|edition=2nd|isbn=978-1579583941|page=365}}\n* {{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=H8mb_JMx4u0C&pg=PA90|title=Second Act Trouble: Behind the Scenes at Broadway's Big Musical Bombs|year=2006|authorlink=Steven Suskin|first=Steven|last=Suskin|publisher=[[Hal Leonard Corporation|Applause Theatre & Cinema Books]]|location=[[Milwaukee]]|edition=Annotated|isbn=978-1557836311|pages=90\u201393}}\n* {{cite news|url=https://www.newspapers.com/newspage/110398031/|title=Life of the Party: The Story of Beatrice|work=[[The Courier-Journal]]|location=[[Louisville, Kentucky]]|author=The Courier-Journal Staff|date=September 19, 1999|accessdate=October 10, 2016|page=195 |url-access=subscription}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Sister project links|commonscat=yes }}\n*{{Amg name|9666}}\n*{{IMDb name|id=993}}\n*{{IBDB name}}\n*[http://www.makers.com/carol-burnett Carol Burnett]  Video produced by ''[[Makers: Women Who Make America]]''\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20050325095723/http://www.topix.net/who/carol-burnett Carol Burnett news] on Topix.net\n*{{The Interviews name}}\n*[https://archive.today/20130204195802/http://www.tvacres.com/music_songs_fool.htm John Foster Dulles song]\n*[http://www.edsullivan.com/artists/carol-burnett Carol Burnett, ''The Ed Sullivan Show'']\n*[http://www.emmys.com/celebrities/carol-burnett Carol Burnett] at Emmys.com\n*[http://www.thespectrum.com/story/entertainment/2017/02/02/fifty-years-carol-burnett-show/97257108/ Interview with Carol Burnett. Accessed February 11, 2017.]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20150920024318/http://www.museum.tv/eotv/burnettcaro.htm Carol Burnett] at The Museum of Broadcast Communications\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title = Awards for Carol Burnett\n|list =\n{{Carol Burnett Award}}\n{{Golden Globe Award Best Actress TV Comedy}}\n{{Grammy Award for Best Spoken Word Album 2010s}}\n{{Hasty Pudding Woman of the Year}}\n{{Kennedy Center Honorees 2000s}}\n{{Mark Twain Prize for American Humor}}\n{{EmmyAward ComedyGuestActress 1976-2000}}\n{{EmmyAward VarietyPerformance 1959\u20131973}}\n{{ScreenActorsGuildAward LifeAchievement}}\n{{Special Tony Award}}\n{{TCA Career Achievement Award}}\n{{1985 Television Hall of Fame}}\n}}\n{{The Carol Burnett Show}}\n{{Portal bar|Biography|Film|Theatre | Comedy | Music|Texas | New York | California |Arts | Television}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Burnett, Carol}}\n[[Category:Carol Burnett| ]]\n[[Category:1933 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses from San Antonio]]\n[[Category:American female singers]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American memoirists]]\n[[Category:American sketch comedians]]\n[[Category:American stage actresses]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:American voice actresses]]\n